I have an issue with the PKC. It seems that the device with FW 2.7.5, which I access through remote admin, replies to me through PSK. I am working on a patch (that seem to work):
```diff
diff --git a/src/mesh/MeshModule.cpp b/src/mesh/MeshModule.cpp
index 409c5217..d93d3428 100644
--- a/src/mesh/MeshModule.cpp
+++ b/src/mesh/MeshModule.cpp
@@ -244,6 +244,10 @@ void setReplyTo(meshtastic_MeshPacket *p, const meshtastic_MeshPacket &to)
     p->to = getFrom(&to);    // Make sure that if we are sending to the local node, we use our local node addr, not 0
     p->channel = to.channel; // Use the same channel that the request came in on
     p->hop_limit = routingModule->getHopLimitForResponse(to.hop_start, to.hop_limit);
+    p->pki_encrypted = to.pki_encrypted;
+    if (p->pki_encrypted) {
+        memcpy(p->public_key.bytes, to.public_key.bytes, 32);
+    }

     // No need for an ack if we are just delivering locally (it just generates an ignored ack)
     p->want_ack = (to.from != 0) ? to.want_ack : false;
```
I am wondering why this is not the default. Is there a better solution?

